properties.description: Posted by Bayareacritic 443 Main Street Pleasanton, CA"Hofbrau in Pleasanton serves deliciously messy sandwiches" My sandwich was just as good as the first time and once again I used every inch of my napkin. When it comes to service – Bert and the cooks on the line are nice and efficient, but it’s basically self service up until you sit and your table. properties.description: Posted by Bayareacritic 127 West Washington Ave. Sunnyvale, CAWhen you go to some select restaurants, it’s immediately apparent that you’re in experienced, professional hands almost the minute you enter. properties.name: Iron Horse Vineyards
properties.description: Posted by Bayareacritic9786 Ross Station Road Sebastopol, caI\'m almost positive I didn\'t pay for the tasting, however, I did join the corral club and will get wine every quarter. This is my favorite winery so far (for tasting). I like to bring the dogs too, so finding great wineries that allow dogs to join you is a rare occassion. Recently, I had a friend bring over a 1996 Blanc do Blanc LD and it was THE BEST SPARKLING WINE I HAVE EVER HAD IN MY LIFE!!!!
